indicator-virtual-box (1.0.15-1) precise; urgency=low

  * Changes for Python3 and PyGObject.
  * Now supports VirtualBox 4.2 and specifically groups.
  * Handle the case when VirtualBox is not installed.
  * Handle the case when VirtualBox is installed but has not yet been run
    (and so $HOME/.VirtualBox/VirtualBox.xml does not exist).
  * Moved the preferences into a tabbed view.
  * Now uses a radio button to indicate a running VM as standard.
    Removed the (legacy) show text before/after a VM.
  * Added option to show text before/after a group name.
  * Known issue: If a VM exists in a group (and there is another VM of the
    same name but not in a group) and you ungroup, the VM in the group is
    not removed from the group.  This appears to be a bug in the VirtualBox
    UI and as such the indicator displays the VM (from the group) alongside
    the other VMs.

 -- Bernard Giannetti <thebernmeister@hotmail.com>  Tue, 6 Nov 2012 18:45:52 +1000


